target_title: msg: Do not call message with out of bounds index

note.body:
The solution here works @danigm. I can confirm it fixes the sample file. However two things came to mind:

- I noticed that fixing the database does not mark the save action as enabled. I fixed this in the latest commit.
- If you manually edit the file to have more plurals than in the config, e.g. modify the following msgid and add plurals 1,2, and 3:

```
msgid "Logged {n_messages} message"
msgid_plural "Logged {n_messages} messages"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""
msgstr[2] ""
msgstr[3] ""
```

the file after saving will be

```
msgid "Logged {n_messages} message"
msgid_plural "Logged {n_messages} messages"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""
```

having one extra plural.

note.body:
This fixes the issue where
- Opening the app
- Open the D-L panel
- Press ESC top close D-L panel
- Open the D-L panel again

would result in a missing back button.

When I discussed the commit that added that code on the libadwaita room, using `adw_navigation_view_replace_with_tags` in this context was a symptom of a bigger navigational issues and perhaps the real solution is more involved, this still gets a +1 on my end.
